---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { getTranslations } from "../i18n/utils";

const locale = "en";
const t = getTranslations(locale);
const canonicalUrl = "https://dokos.app/privacy";
const lastUpdated = "February 26, 2026";
---

<BaseLayout locale={locale} t={t}>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <title>Privacy Policy — Dokos</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Privacy Policy for Dokos — a local-first document reader. We do not collect, transmit, or store any of your documents or personal data." />
    <link rel="canonical" href={canonicalUrl} />
    <meta name="robots" content="index, follow" />
  </Fragment>

  <div class="min-h-screen bg-background-light dark:bg-background-dark py-16 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">

      <div class="mb-10">
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-primary hover:underline text-sm font-medium mb-8">
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7" />
          </svg>
          Back to Dokos
        </a>

        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-6 mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose prose-slate dark:prose-invert max-w-none space-y-8 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">

        <section>
          <p class="text-lg">
            At <strong>Dokos</strong> ("we", "our", or "us"), your privacy is a top priority.
            This Privacy Policy explains how we handle information when you use the Dokos desktop application
            and visit our website at <a href="https://dokos.app" class="text-primary hover:underline">https://dokos.app</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-3">1. Data Collection</h2>
          <p>
            Dokos is a <strong>local-first application</strong>. All file processing happens entirely on your device.
            We do <strong>not</strong> collect, transmit, or store any of your documents, files, or personal data on our servers.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            We do not collect:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
            <li>The contents of any files you open or edit</li>
            <li>Your name, email address, or any personally identifiable information</li>
            <li>Location data</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">
            The application does collect <strong>anonymous usage telemetry</strong> to help us improve Dokos.
            See Section 4 for details on how telemetry works and how to disable it.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-3">2. Local Storage</h2>
          <p>
            Any preferences and application settings (such as theme selection or window size) are stored
            <strong>locally on your device</strong> using standard OS mechanisms. This data never leaves your machine.
            We do not use cookies or tracking technologies within the application.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-3">3. Website Analytics</h2>
          <p>
            Our website (<a href="https://dokos.app" class="text-primary hover:underline">dokos.app</a>) uses
            <strong>Umami Analytics</strong>, a privacy-focused, open-source analytics solution. Umami does not
            use cookies and does not collect any personally identifiable information. It only collects
            aggregated, anonymous page view statistics to help us understand which content is most useful.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-3">4. App Telemetry (Aptabase)</h2>
          <p>
            Dokos uses <strong>Aptabase</strong>, a privacy-first, open-source analytics platform, to collect
            anonymous usage telemetry. This helps us understand which features are most used and improve the
            application over time.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">What Aptabase collects:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
            <li>Anonymous event names (e.g., which viewers are opened)</li>
            <li>Operating system and app version</li>
            <li>Country-level location (derived from IP, not stored)</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">What Aptabase does <strong>not</strong> collect:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
            <li>The contents of any files you open</li>
            <li>Any personally identifiable information</li>
            <li>Persistent device identifiers or fingerprints</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">
            Aptabase is designed to be <strong>GDPR-compliant</strong> and does not build user profiles or
            share data with third parties. You can learn more at
            <a href="https://aptabase.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary hover:underline">aptabase.com</a>.
          </p>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-4 mb-2">Opting Out</h3>
          <p>
            Telemetry is <strong>opt-out</strong>. You can disable it at any time in two ways:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
            <li><strong>On first launch</strong> — a prompt lets you enable or disable telemetry before any data is sent</li>
            <li><strong>At any time</strong> — go to <em>Settings → Privacy</em> and toggle telemetry off</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">
            When telemetry is disabled, no data is sent to Aptabase or any other service.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-3">5. Distribution Channels</h2>
          <p>
            The Dokos application is distributed through:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
            <li><strong>Microsoft Store</strong> — subject to Microsoft's own privacy policy</li>
            <li><strong>Direct download</strong> from dokos.app — no account required</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">
            When you download via the Microsoft Store, Microsoft may collect data as per their
            <a href="https://privacy.microsoft.com/en-us/privacystatement" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary hover:underline">Privacy Statement</a>.
            We do not control or have access to any such data.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-3">6. Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p>
            Dokos is not directed at children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect any personal
            information from children. Since we collect no personal data at all, Dokos is safe for users of all ages.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-3">7. Data Security</h2>
          <p>
            Because we do not collect or store your data, there is no personal data at risk on our end.
            Your files and preferences remain on your device and are protected by your operating system's
            own security mechanisms.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-3">8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p>
            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page
            with an updated "Last updated" date. We encourage you to review this policy periodically.
            Continued use of the application after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-3">9. Contact Us</h2>
          <p>
            If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            <strong>Dokos</strong><br />
            Email: <a href="mailto:dokos@aibana.studio" class="text-primary hover:underline [unicode-bidi:bidi-override] [direction:rtl]"><span aria-hidden="true" class="absolute opacity-0 pointer-events-none select-none">oitneves</span>oiduts.anab<span aria-hidden="true" class="absolute opacity-0 pointer-events-none select-none">xzq</span>ia@sokod</a><br />
            Website: <a href="https://dokos.app" class="text-primary hover:underline">https://dokos.app</a>
          </p>
        </section>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
